{"cells":[{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"# Lesson 9: Page Redirects and Dynamic Params ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In this lesson, you'll create a turbine-specific details page and implement navigation to it from the map. You'll configure the **View Details** button to redirect users and learn how to read URL parameters from Redux to display turbine information.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Learning Objectives","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"After completing this lesson, you will be able to:\n- Dispatch navigation actions to redirect between pages.\n- Define routes with dynamic URL parameters.\n- Read URL parameters from the Redux store.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Estimated Time","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"This lesson will take approximately **20 minutes** to complete.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Lab Support","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"For support, check out the <a href=\"https://learn.c3.ai/page/help-center\" target=\"_blank\">Help Center</a> information.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 1: Create the WindTurbine-specific page ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Let's start by creating the shell of the WindTurbine-specific page. \n\nIn `ui/c3/src/customInstances`, create a new file `WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx`.\n\nCopy and paste the following code snippet in <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\nimport React from \"react\";\n\nconst WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n   return <h1>Hello, World!</h1>;\n};\n\nexport default WindTurbineSpecificPage;","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 2: Create a redirect","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Recall the popup that appears when you select a marker on the map:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-9/popup.png\" width=\"350px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Currently, the **View Details** button does nothing. Let's add some functionality to it. When a user selects the **View Details** button for a turbine, we want to redirect them to the turbine-specific page.\n\nWe will accomplish this by using the `useDispatch` hook. \n\nAdd the following import to <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/components/WindTurbinePopup.tsx\"><code>WindTurbinePopup.tsx</code></a>:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbinePopup.tsx\n*/\n\nimport { useDispatch } from '@c3/ui/UiSdlUseDispatch';","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Next, implement the `handleViewDetails` function. This function dispatches a `GLOBAL_REDIRECT` action that navigates to the turbine-specific page with the turbine's ID in the URL.\n\nCopy and paste the following code snippet into <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/components/WindTurbinePopup.tsx\"><code>WindTurbinePopup.tsx</code></a>:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbinePopup.tsx\n*/\n\n// const WindTurbinePopup = ({ turbine }: WindTurbinePopupProps) => {\n    // ...\n\n    const dispatch = useDispatch();\n    \n    const handleViewDetails = (turbine: WindTurbine) => {\n        dispatch({\n        type: 'GLOBAL_REDIRECT',\n        payload: {\n            url: `/windturbine/${turbine.id}`, // url with page param, passing the turbine id\n        },\n        });\n    };\n\n    // return (\n    // ...\n// };","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Notice that `turbine.id` is passed as a URL parameter in `/windturbine/${turbine.id}`. The framework automatically stores URL parameters in Redux, which allows us to access this ID in Part 4 when building the turbine-specific page.\n\nLastly, we need to add `onClick` behavior to the button in the component. When a user clicks the button, it should dispatch the `GLOBAL_REDIRECT` action. Add the `onClick` attribute to the button in <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/components/WindTurbinePopup.tsx\"><code>WindTurbinePopup.tsx</code></a>:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbinePopup.tsx\n*/\n\n// const WindTurbinePopup = ({ turbine }: WindTurbinePopupProps) => {\n//   ...\n//\n//   return (\n//    <Popup>\n//     ...\n//        <button\n            onClick={() => handleViewDetails(turbine)}\n//          className=\"view-details-btn\"\n//          onMouseOver={(e) => {\n//            e.currentTarget.style.backgroundColor = '#1d4ed8';\n//          }}\n//          onMouseOut={(e) => {\n//            e.currentTarget.style.backgroundColor = '#2563eb';\n//          }}\n//        >\n//          View Details\n//        </button>\n//    ...        \n//    </Popup>\n//  );\n//};","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 3: Add a route with a dynamic URL parameter","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"In Part 2, we dispatched a navigation action with the URL `/windturbine/${turbine.id}`. Now we need to register this dynamic route.\n\nIn the following code snippet, we define a route with `{{turbineId}}`. This tells the framework:\n1. This route accepts a dynamic parameter.\n2. Extract the value from the URL (e.g., `123` from `/windturbine/123`).\n3. Store it in Redux under `pageParams.turbineId`.\n4. Render `WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx` when this route is accessed.\n\nCopy and paste the following line into  <a href=\"../../metadata/UiSdlRoute/UiRoute.csv\"><code>metadata/UISdlRoute/UiRoute.csv</code></a>.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"plaintext","value":"# Paste in `metadata/UISdlRoute/UiRoute.csv`\n\nWindTurbine,SpecificPage,/windturbine/{{turbineId}},/windturbine/{{turbineId}}","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Checkpoint: Verify redirect ","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Refresh the UI and click a marker to open the popup. When you select the **View Details** button, you should be routed to the WindTurbine-specific page with the turbine ID in the URL.\n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-9/redirect-parameter-only.png\" width=\"750px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"## Part 4: Read the parameter from Redux\n","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"The framework automatically adds URL parameters to the Redux store. Similar to accessing the Redux store in <a href=\"../redux-actions-and-reducers/08-read-from-redux.c3nb\">Lesson 8</a>, we'll do the following in <code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code>:\n\n1. Declare the `ImmutableReduxState` type to access the Redux state safely.\n2. Define the `turbineDataSelector` function to specify the path to the turbine ID in the store.\n3. Call the `useSelectedState` hook to retrieve the ID value and use it throughout the page.\n\nBegin by adding the following imports in <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n// Add to imports at top of the file\nimport { UiSdlReduxState } from '@c3/types';\nimport { useSelectedState } from '@c3/ui/UiSdlUseData';","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"The following code retrieves the turbine ID from `pageParams.turbineId` in Redux and displays it on the page. Copy and paste it into <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx</code></a>:","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":2,"languageId":"typescriptreact","value":"/*\n  WindTurbine.SpecificPage.tsx\n*/\n\n// const WindTurbineSpecificPage = () => {\n\n      type ImmutableReduxState = Map<keyof UiSdlReduxState, UiSdlReduxState[keyof UiSdlReduxState]>;\n\n      const turbineDataSelector = (state: ImmutableReduxState) => {\n        return state.getIn(['pageParams', 'turbineId']) || null;\n      };\n\n      const turbineIdFromState = useSelectedState(turbineDataSelector, (prev: any, next: any) => prev === next);\n\n      return <h1>Hello, World! You are viewing turbine id {turbineIdFromState}</h1>\n// };\n\n// export default WindTurbineSpecificPage;","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Checkpoint: Verify displayed parameter","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"Navigate to a turbine-specific page. You should see the turbine ID from the URL displayed as text on the page.\n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-9/verify-displayed-parameter.png\" width=\"750px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"-----","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"### Summary","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"You created a turbine-specific page, dispatched navigation, defined a dynamic route with `{{turbineId}}`, and read the ID from Redux to drive the page.","output":[],"executionSummary":{}},{"kind":1,"languageId":"markdown","value":"<div style=\"display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:16px; margin-top:24px; align-items:center; width:100%;\">\n  <a href=\"../redux-actions-and-reducers/08-read-from-redux.c3nb\"\n     aria-label=\"Go to Lesson 7: Read from Redux\"\n     style=\"display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:10px 16px; border-radius:10px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600; border:1px solid #d0d7de; background:#f6f8fa; color:#0b1026; box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;\">\n    ← Previous: Read from Redux\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"./10-create-turbine-dashboard.c3nb\"\n     aria-label=\"Go to Lesson 9: Create a Turbine Dashboard\"\n     style=\"display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:10px 16px; border-radius:10px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600; border:1px solid #1f6feb; background:#1f6feb; color:#ffffff; box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;\">\n    Next: Create a Turbine Dashboard →\n  </a>\n</div>","output":[],"executionSummary":{}}],"metadata":{"id":"131be1eb-f1c9-445f-b1ce-2e5083da7551","serializerVersion":"1","runtime":"js-rhino"}}